  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Classes bundle data and behavior into reusable blueprints; objects are live instances with their own state. In agent systems, classes model tools, clients, conversation sessions, and execution contexts — turning ad hoc dicts into structured, testable components."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " defines attributes (data) and methods (functions on that data). An "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "object",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (instance) is created by calling the class like a function: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session = AgentSession(id=\"run-1\")",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Minimal class example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class ToolResult:\n    def __init__(self, ok: bool, data: object = None, error: str | None = None):\n        self.ok = ok\n        self.data = data\n        self.error = error\n\n    def to_message(self) -> dict:\n        if self.ok:\n            return {\"role\": \"tool\", \"content\": str(self.data)}\n        return {\"role\": \"tool\", \"content\": f\"Error: {self.error}\"}\n\nresult = ToolResult(ok=True, data=[\"doc-1\", \"doc-2\"])"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agents accumulate state across turns: messages, tool outputs, budgets, metadata. Classes enforce invariants (a session always has an ID), encapsulate methods ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session.add_turn",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "), and enable polymorphic tool implementations behind a shared interface."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Structure",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — fields and methods colocated with clear intent"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reuse",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — instantiate many sessions from one class definition"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Testing",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — mock "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "LLMClient",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " subclasses in unit tests"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "IDE support",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — autocomplete on attributes and methods"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ceremony",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — simple record-like data may not need a full class (see Dataclasses topic)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mutable state",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — shared object references can leak across requests if not isolated"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-engineering",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — not every helper needs a class hierarchy"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "__init__ and instance attributes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class AgentSession:\n    def __init__(self, session_id: str, model: str = \"gpt-4o\"):\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        self.model = model\n        self.messages: list[dict] = []\n        self.tokens_used = 0\n\n    def add_message(self, role: str, content: str) -> None:\n        self.messages.append({\"role\": role, \"content\": content})"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instance vs. class attributes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class BaseTool:\n    category = \"general\"  # class attribute — shared default\n\n    def __init__(self, name: str):\n        self.name = name  # instance attribute — per object\n\nsearch = BaseTool(\"search\")\ncalc = BaseTool(\"calculator\")\nsearch.category = \"retrieval\"  # does not change calc.category"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Methods and self"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The first parameter of instance methods is conventionally "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "self",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — the instance receiving the call. Python passes it automatically: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session.add_message(\"user\", \"hi\")",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " binds "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "self",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a class",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when data and behavior belong together and persist across multiple operations"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use a class",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for agent clients, sessions, tool wrappers with configuration"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefer functions or dicts",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for stateless one-shot transforms"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How to implement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class SearchTool:\n    def __init__(self, retriever, top_k: int = 5):\n        self.retriever = retriever\n        self.top_k = top_k\n\n    def __call__(self, query: str) -> list[str]:\n        return self.retriever.search(query, limit=self.top_k)\n\nsearch = SearchTool(retriever)\nids = search(\"agent memory\")  # callable tool instance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class TokenBudget:\n    def __init__(self, limit: int):\n        self.limit = limit\n        self.spent = 0\n\n    def charge(self, n: int) -> bool:\n        if self.spent + n > self.limit:\n            return False\n        self.spent += n\n        return True\n\n    @property\n    def remaining(self) -> int:\n        return self.limit - self.spent"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An agent runner class owns the message list, budget, and client — the core loop mutates instance state each turn:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class AgentRunner:\n    def __init__(self, client, system_prompt: str, budget: TokenBudget):\n        self.client = client\n        self.budget = budget\n        self.messages = [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt}]\n\n    def step(self, user_input: str) -> str:\n        self.messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_input})\n        resp = self.client.complete(self.messages)\n        if not self.budget.charge(resp.total_tokens):\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Budget exceeded\")\n        self.messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": resp.text})\n        return resp.text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Forgetting self",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "def add(self, x): self.items.append(x)",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", not "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "items.append(x)",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shared mutable class attributes",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — lists/dicts as class attrs shared across instances"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "God objects",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — one class doing client, tools, logging, and persistence"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "One class, one responsibility — session state vs. API client vs. tool registry"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Initialize all instance fields in "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "__init__",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for predictable object shape"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefer composition ("
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "self.client",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ") over giant monolithic classes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A class is a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cookie cutter",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "; each object is a cookie with the same shape but its own decoration (attribute values). Methods are actions each cookie can perform on itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Classes combine state and behavior for agent sessions, tools, and clients"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Instances are created with "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "ClassName(...)",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "; methods take "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "self",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Separate concerns — avoid monolithic agent classes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Watch shared mutable state across instances and requests"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
